After clinching the coveted Tropika Island of Treasure title in season 8, Brendan Peyper is elated to be making a return on Tropika Island of Treasure: All-stars. The singer along with his teammate Lisanne Lazarus was announced as the 2018 Tropika Island of Treasure champions. Peyper shared details about his experience on the island revealing all that he learnt while in the run for the 1 million grand prize. He said he had agreed to come back on the show because of the “awesome” experience he had had on the island. “I just remember the awesome experience it was being on an island in the middle of nowhere and being able to participate in this crazy competition.” said Peyper It may seem to viewers that the competition is just about winning, but Peyper revealed that it was also a learning experience and how to deal with tough situations. “(Its about) being able to stay focused and positive when things get tough.” As for the fun bits, he said: “ Definitely being able to chill in the clear water and cooling off when you need to. And also the food was amazing.” On the question, of having a strategy to win the game, Peyper said he would do things the same way he did the last time around.. ” I’ll just stick to my guns and do me like I did last time, and hope for the best. Mainly enjoy every second.” The other celebrity contestants for the All-Star season are Khanya Mkangisa, Karlien van Jaarsveld, Jonathan Boynton-Lee, Nay Maps, Roxy Louw, Maurice Paige, Kelly Khumalo, and Shashi Naidoo. While the previous seasons boasted some stunning stays in luxuriant tropical locations from the Maldives to Zanzibar, Mauritius, Phuket, Mexico, Jamaica, Seychelles, and Curacao in  the Caribbean, this year's location is yet to be revealed. This new season promises to bring more fascinating adventures for viewers to look forward to seeing on their screens.